HEADWORD: fairy-slipper
<hw>fairy-slipper</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a rare north temperate bog
orchid (<spn>Calypso bulbosa</spn>) bearing a solitary white to pink
flower marked with purple at the tip of an erect reddish stalk above one
basal leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> calypso, <spn>Calypso bulbosa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fairy tale</ent>⟦br⟧
